DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Cerebrospinal Fluid Alpha-Fetoprotein Outcome Date
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The date on which information related to result of procedure that involves testing of alpha-fetoprotein, a protein normally produced by a developing fetus, from the fluid flowing around the brain and spinal cord is obtained.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Information related to result of procedure that involves testing of alpha-fetoprotein, a protein normally produced by a developing fetus, from the fluid flowing around the brain and spinal cord.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: (seh-REE-broe-SPY-nal) The fluid flowing around the brain and spinal cord. Cerebrospinal fluid is produced in the ventricles in the brain.:Alpha-fetoprotein. A protein normally produced by a developing fetus. AFP levels are usually undetectable in the blood of healthy nonpregnant adults. An elevated level of AFP suggests the presence of either a primary liver cancer or germ cell tumor.:The result of an action.

Concepts.definition: The fluid that is contained within the brain ventricles, the subarachnoid space and the central canal of the spinal cord.
Alpha-fetoprotein (609 aa, ~69 kDa) is encoded by the human AFP gene. This protein plays a role in the binding to copper, nickel, bilirubin and fatty acids in the fetal circulation.
